The cource gives a survey about the main changes of the Estonian language during the different peroids of the history.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Introduction to the historical formation of the Estonian language.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student completing the course knows the most important research methods of language history; has an overview of the social status and uses of the Estonian language in different centuries; knows and can characterize the main lexical strata; can describe the development of noun and verb categories; knows how the morphological type of the Estonian language has changed historically; knows the main sound changes in the history of the Estonian language and can reconstruct the noun and verb forms of the late Finnic.
